This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for text analysis. Specifically, it presents a novel algorithm for corpus-based term set expansion, which involves identifying related terms to a given set of terms. This is a common task in NLP and information retrieval (IR) applications. The paper also introduces a new dataset for evaluating term set expansion algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and IR topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning), which are all relevant to the paper's methodology and evaluation.
